subSubSection.paragraph:
This new species resembles 
Dinotrema sylvestre
Tobias but differs in having the mesoscutal pit present (absent in 
Dinotrema sylvestre
), mandible 1.55-1.60 times as long as wide (as long as wide in 
Dinotrema sylvestre
), first flagellar segment 4.25 times as long as wide (3.50 times in 
Dinotrema sylvestre
), middle flagellar segments 3 times as long as their width (2.00 times in 
Dinotrema sylvestre
) and hind femur 5.00 times as long as its maximum width (4.00 times in 
Dinotrema sylvestre
).
